data(economics, package = "ggplot2")

m1$set(pointSize = 0, lineWidth = 1)

m1$show("iframesrc", cdn = TRUE)

library(ggplot2)
Warning: package 'ggplot2' was built under R version 3.1.2
library(grid)
library(scales)
pushViewport(viewport(layout = grid.layout(6, 1)))

myplot1 <- ggplot(datatest_selb,aes(date))+geom_line(color="Red",aes(y=Temperature))+ylab("Temperature")+xlab("Time")+
                        scale_x_datetime(breaks=date_breaks("30 min"),labels=date_format("%H:%M"))+
                        theme(axis.text.x=element_text(angle=90,hjust=1))        
        
myplot2 <- ggplot(datatest_selb,aes(date))+geom_line(color="Blue",aes(y=Humidity))+ylab("Humidity")+xlab("Time")+
        scale_x_datetime(breaks=date_breaks("30 min"),labels=date_format("%H:%M"))+
        theme(axis.text.x=element_text(angle=90,hjust=1))        

myplot3 <- ggplot(datatest_selb,aes(date))+geom_line(color="deepskyblue1",aes(y=HumidityRatio))+ylab("HumidityRatio")+xlab("Time")+
        scale_x_datetime(breaks=date_breaks("30 min"),labels=date_format("%H:%M"))+
        theme(axis.text.x=element_text(angle=90,hjust=1))        

myplot4 <- ggplot(datatest_selb,aes(date))+geom_line(color="Green",aes(y=CO2))+ylab("CO2 (ppm)")+xlab("Time")+
        scale_x_datetime(breaks=date_breaks("30 min"),labels=date_format("%H:%M"))+
        theme(axis.text.x=element_text(angle=90,hjust=1))        

myplot5 <- ggplot(datatest_selb,aes(date))+geom_line(color="gold4",aes(y=Light))+ylab("Light (Lux)")+xlab("Time")+
        scale_x_datetime(breaks=date_breaks("30 min"),labels=date_format("%H:%M"))+
        theme(axis.text.x=element_text(angle=90,hjust=1))        


print(myplot1, vp = viewport(layout.pos.row = 1, layout.pos.col = 1))
print(myplot2, vp = viewport(layout.pos.row = 2, layout.pos.col = 1))
print(myplot3, vp = viewport(layout.pos.row = 3, layout.pos.col = 1))
print(myplot4, vp = viewport(layout.pos.row = 4, layout.pos.col = 1))
print(myplot5, vp = viewport(layout.pos.row = 5, layout.pos.col = 1))
